I think we need to have

`conf.get('polling_batch_size')` here and pass it down into the template even if it is None.

I would like to avoid hard-coding a magic number in the agent charm code since there is already an upstream default in Ceilometer itself: 

    cfg.IntOpt('batch_size', default=50, help='Batch size of samples to send to notification agent, '
'Set to 0 to disable'),


In essence, if this config is not provided via a relation with ceilometer, the charm would not render this config at all:

[polling]
{% if polling_batch_size -%}
batch_size = {{ polling_batch_size }}
{% endif -%}

